*  df -h   ---to see the mount volume
*  findmnt  ---- to see the filesystem format
*  lsblk   ----to list the volumes
*  file -s /dev/xvdf  --- to see the data in volume
*  mkfs -t ext4 /dev/xvdf   --- to format the volume
*  mkdir /nagendra   --- create the directory name for volume
*  mount /dev/xvdf /nagendra/   --- mount the volume
*  cd /nagendra   ---- to enter into volum
*  vi /etc/fstab   ---- edit the fstab to make volume attach permanent
   { /dev/xvdf              /nagendra ext4   defaults                0 0  }
* sudo mount -o remount/   ---- to remount the volume when we get any issues
* umount -a    --- to unmount the volume